{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fda81ba5-0e30-42ad-97e4-604fc0916620","content":"No workflow files here, so I'll give you the general guidance for switching to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n## Changes needed:\n\n**1. On nuget.org** — Register your package's trusted publisher:\n- Go to your package → Manage → Publishing → Add Trusted Publisher\n- Specify your GitHub repo owner, repo name, workflow filename, and optionally an environment\n\n**2. In your GitHub Actions workflow:**\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write  # Required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n    # Optional but recommended: tie to a GitHub Environment\n    environment: nuget-publish\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n\n      - name: Push to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n          --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Key differences from your current setup:**\n| Before | After |\n|--------|-------|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` passed via `--api-key` | No `--api-key` needed |\n| No special permissions | `id-token: write` required |\n| Secret rotation burden | Credential-free, OIDC-based |\n\n**3. Remove** the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo settings once verified.\n\nThe `dotnet nuget push` CLI automatically uses the OIDC token when no API key is provided and the `id-token: write` permission is set. Make sure you're using .NET SDK 8.0.400+ or the `nuget` CLI 6.12+.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"86becad6-459f-45a8-9615-08cf5c2ff0dd","outputTokens":408,"requestId":"101E:2FF63B:2A135DC:2E5D031:69FD3443"},"id":"5e34ddb2-990f-4099-9d48-91dec1d36065","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:54:37.926Z","parentId":"12d572ed-e771-4099-b524-c6374af81c94"}
